                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d159">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-03-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At our interview to-day Lord Kimberley gave me a copy of latest proposed
                    agreement between you and British ambassador at Washington as to close season
                    north of 42°, commencing May. As the United States have every possible interest
                    for immediate legislation to enforce award, I would accept Lord Kimberley’s
                    amendment suggesting that close season shall cease August 1 as to that power
                    which has then prepared by its legislation to enforce award. Notice has been
                    given last week of introduction of bill next Thursday in the House of Commons by
                    the attorney-general, who drafted it; no opposition anticipated. Am satisfied
                    Lord Kimberley is as anxious as ourselves to secure honorable execution of
                    award.</p>
            </div>
